Any.description:
`Any` contains an arbitrary serialized message along with a
URL that describes the type of the serialized message

@type.description: A URL/resource name that uniquely identifies the type of the serialized message.

timeseriesv1AccessType.description:
Access Type Enum
 Specifies the level of entitlement on the timeseries as either read only or
 read and write.

 - ACCESS_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED: ACTION_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED
 - ACCESS_TYPE_READ: String constant value READ
 - ACCESS_TYPE_WRITE: String constant value WRITE

v1FilterTimeseriesEntitlementsRequest.title: The Request body for Filter TimeseriesEntitlement

query.description:
The query used to filter against TimeseriesEntitlement, such as
timeseries_id, entitlement name, read or write access, etc.

pageToken.description: The starting point of a query result.

pageSize.description:
The maximum number of TimeseriesEntitlements to be returned per page of
results. The page size is 1000. Otherwise, the maximum allowed page size is
100.

Default is 100 if empty or a number < 1 is specified.

v1FilterTimeseriesEntitlementsResponse.title: The Response body for Filter TimeseriesEntitlement

timeseriesEntitlements.description:
The TimeseriesEntitlement entities that match the specified
FilterTimeseriesEntitlementRequest.

nextPageToken.title: next page token for result list

v1TimeseriesEntitlement.title: Resource for TimeseriesEntitlement related to a TimeseriesMetadata Object
